A total of 4,025 villages in 114 districts of 21 provinces flooded
A total of 4,025 villages in 114 districts of 21 provinces have been hit by floods, affecting 604,788 people, Chatchai Promlert, director general of the Disaster Prevention and Mitigation Department, said on Tuesday.
The flood affected provinces are Phitsanulok, Phichit, Kamphaengphet, Petchabun, Nakhon Ratchasima, Surin, Kalasin, Si Sa Ket, Ubon Ratchathani, Amnatcharoen, Buri Ram, Nakhon Sawan, Saraburi, Lopburi, Kanchanaburi, Nakhon Nayok, Ayutthaya, Angthong, Prachinburi, Sakaeo and Chumphon, he said.